[div class=p 
	"Basic Bot with TasStudio
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	(youtube|v=-6XmOtPlvRY)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Notes
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		"-Check Memory Domain
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"-Check Byte Length
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"-Check that the Fitness Function (the Conditions) Make Sense.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"TasStudio can be used if you have BizHawk in the Recording Mode.  Otherwise it will simply playback what is is in the TasStudio Piano Roll.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Make Sure you select the Correct "Slot" Aka Save State.  If you are not using TasStudio this is just a Save State Slot.  For Tas Studios it is a Branch #.  Ex:Slot = 0 would be Branch #0.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"The input is in percentages.  For unlikely input I suggest very low percentages 0.1% to 0.2%. 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"After finding a good series of input.  Press STOP.  Then Press "Play" in the  "Best" group section.  Then on the Branch select the Update button (the red recycle icon?).  Then save.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"After finishing make sure to put Bizhawk back to the PlayBack Mode.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Then you should clean up the input only leaving the minimum input to achieve the fast time.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[h3 id=PossibleIssues 
	"Possible issues
	$LF
]h3
[ol 
	[li 
		" Conditions do not fire.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"Close and Restart Basic Bot.  Just set it up anew.  
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" Conditions Always Are True.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"You probably have a bad condition.  I had this with a bad Tie Condition.  I was trying to use a timer but at the end it was always the same value and I was using Less Than Or Equal To for the first condition.  It seems to evaluate the tie condition at the end number of frames.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" Ending Frame after Playback is after expected end.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"I had this happen a couple times.  I would manually put the branch back a couple frames then run it.  This seemed to let it work correctly.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" After Playback values are different.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"Look up at 3 should be a similar issue.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" Bot never finds a solution.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"If this is the case you have the number of frames it runs too high.  This is a dumb bot and does not learn.  The default 100 frames seems like a good amount to get good results.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" How to Switch Between Recording and Playback.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"My shortcut button is 'q'.  You can view what yours is if you go to the menu "Configure Hotkeys" - Movie - "Toggle read-only".
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
]ol
[hr 
